subSubSection.paragraph:
The dentary bears 26‒30 (27.67 ± 1.63; n = 6) tooth loci (
Fig. 10A, D
). Laterally, the dentary bears 5‒7 (5.67 ± 0.82; n = 6) mental foramina, which lie in a longitudinal series between the second or third (2.83 ± 0.41; n = 6) and twentieth to twenty-fourth (22.17 ± 1.47; n = 6) tooth loci (
Fig. 10C
). The surangular is completely fused with the compound bone and not distinguishable in MHNLS 21643 (
Fig. 10
) and MHNLS 22711, whereas a soft suture is visible in MHNLS 22712. The anterior process of the compound bone anteriorly surpasses the anteromedial process of the coronoid + splenial complex. However, this anterior extension is only visible when the dentary is (digitally) removed.

